# AI Pedagogical Platform — API Setup Guide

## What you have after this setup
- Your existing Streamlit app (`app.py`) works exactly as before
- A new FastAPI server (`api.py`) runs alongside it
- Any external platform can call your API via HTTP

---

## STEP 1 — Install dependencies

Open a terminal in the folder where your files live and run:

```bash
pip install fastapi uvicorn[standard] pymupdf langchain-ollama langchain-core pydantic
```

Or install everything from the requirements file:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## STEP 2 — Make sure Ollama is running

Your API uses Gemma locally via Ollama.
In a separate terminal, start Ollama:

```bash
ollama serve
```

Make sure Gemma is pulled:

```bash
ollama pull gemma3:4b
```

---

## STEP 3 — Start the API server

```bash
uvicorn api:app --reload --port 8000
```

You will see:
```
INFO:     Uvicorn running on http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

Your API is now live. Open http://127.0.0.1:8000 in your browser to confirm.

---

## STEP 4 — Explore the interactive docs

FastAPI generates automatic documentation.
Open in your browser:

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
```

You can test every endpoint directly from the browser — upload a PDF, call /grade, etc.

