## STEP 5 — Test the API with curl

### Test /digitize (upload an exam PDF):
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/digitize \
  -F "file=@your_exam.pdf" \
  -F "dpi=150"
```

Response:
```json
{
  "total": 40,
  "questions": [
    {
      "number": 1,
      "stem": "The diagram shows a plant. Which characteristic...",
      "type": "MCQ",
      "options": { "A": "excretion", "B": "reproduction", "C": "respiration", "D": "sensitivity" },
      "page": 1
    },
    ...
  ],
  "pages": ["data:image/png;base64,...", ...],
  "figures": { "1": [{ "x": 120, "y": 80, "w": 300, "h": 200 }] }
}
```

### Test /grade (grade a student answer):
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/grade \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "question_stem": "Why do plants need nitrate ions?",
    "student_answer": "Plants need nitrates to make proteins.",
    "reference_answer": "Nitrogen is a component of amino acids used to build proteins."
  }'
```

Response:
```json
{
  "score": 16,
  "feedback": "Good answer. You identified the link to proteins but missed amino acids specifically.",
  "missing_concepts": ["amino acids", "nitrogen as component"]
}
```

