## STEP 6 — Share with another developer (local network)

To let someone on the same network use your API, start with:

```bash
uvicorn api:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

Find your local IP:
- Mac/Linux: `ifconfig | grep inet`
- Windows: `ipconfig`

Tell them to call:
```
http://YOUR_IP_ADDRESS:8000
```

---

## STEP 7 — Deploy to the internet (so anyone can use it)

### Option A — Railway (easiest, free tier available)
1. Create account at https://railway.app
2. Push your code to GitHub
3. Connect the GitHub repo to Railway
4. Set start command: `uvicorn api:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT`
5. Railway gives you a public URL like: `https://your-app.railway.app`

### Option B — Render (also free tier)
1. Create account at https://render.com
2. New Web Service → connect GitHub repo
3. Build command: `pip install -r requirements.txt`
4. Start command: `uvicorn api:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT`

### Option C — Your own server (VPS)
```bash
# On the server:
git clone your-repo
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn api:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

Note: For cloud deployment, Ollama needs to run on the same server,
or you can swap it for the Anthropic API / OpenAI API instead.

